(41, 10, 48, 40, 19, 13, 13, 'have mercy on me', 'Children and Mercy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the need for mercy and the importance of approaching Jesus with humility. In Mark, the plea for mercy is made by a blind man, while in Matthew, children are brought to Jesus, highlighting innocence and dependence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 48, 41, 5, 35, 35, 'have mercy on me', 'Desperation for Healing', 'Both passages emphasize a sense of urgency in seeking help from Jesus. In Mark 10:48, the blind man cries out for mercy, while in Mark 5:35, the ruler is told not to trouble Jesus further after his daughter has died, highlighting the desperation in both situations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
